body:
### Version Number

7.15.2

### Codesandbox/Expo snack

https://codesandbox.io/s/react-hook-form-usefieldarray-forked-so681?file=/src/index.js

### Steps to reproduce

I have initialized a react hook form which data is structured like this:
```
const formHook = useForm({
  defaultValues: {
    tripType: "RETURN",
    routes: [
      {
        uuid: "fdsafdas-324234",
        origin: "",
        destination: "",
        departureDate: "09.09.2021",
        returnDate: "17.09.2021"
      }
    ],
    travelers: []
  }
});
```

At the moment I am displaying only 2 fields. One for the `destination` and one for `departureDate`.

 In order to render `destination` I am using `Controller`:
```
<Controller
  render={({ field }) => <input {...field} />}
  name={`routes.${index}.origin`}
  control={control}
/>
```

Because of better code organization I moved `departureDate` in separate component:
```
function Dates({ control, getValues, index }) {
  console.log(JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(getValues())));
  return (
    <Controller
      render={({ field }) => <input {...field} />}
      name={`routes.${index}.departureDate`}
      control={control}
    />
  );
}
```

As you can see I am trying to output `getValues()`. On my surprise I am getting back only `origin` field and no others that were initialized by default values:

<img width="556" alt="Screenshot 2021-09-10 at 00 24 31" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/311634/132770705-c0181d17-c56a-4ae2-8f28-e3c898329ce8.png">

I tried to comment out `Controller` which controls `origin`. I got back all values. My conclusion is that `Controller` somehow breaks the values.

You can reproduce this issue on attached codesandbox link.

### Expected behaviour

The `getValues` method should return everything what was set as a default value.

### What browsers are you seeing the problem on?

Chrome

